[SN]TITLE[SN]
International Women's Day: The women who live tweeted an abortion

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Every day roughly 12 women travel from Ireland to Great Britain for an abortion. On 8 March, some women across Ireland are striking to call on the government to change Ireland's law. The country's constitution puts equal value on the life of the mother and foetus.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
7 March 2017 Last updated at 19:48 GMT
Last summer two young women live tweeted @twowomentravel their journey and now tell their story to the BBC.
